      "date": "2017-08-15 09:19:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> I'd suggest to implement \"fast path\" where uptodate bit is checked with the lock first, otherwise the lock can get contended in some cases. if the bit is set after initialization, then we should be fine?\n\nYes, we need some \"fast path\" to avoid unnecessary lock contention. This patch will NOT be the finial solution, we will use it as temporary solution for LU-9410. If it works, then we can optimize the patch.\n\nWhat I more concern it the 2nd fix. I found that for very rare case, the free block count in the just-initialized group is zero. That seems NOT reasonable and directly caused the subsequent ldiskfs_mb_check_ondisk_bitmap() error.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
